Kenya Airways has renewed its codeshare agreement with EgyptAir on the Nairobi-Cairo route as it seeks to improve connectivity in North Africa.The deal, effective June 1, has enabled enable KQ to resume direct flights to Cairo after they were suspended in August 2013. The codeshare partnership will initially cover six routes including Cairo, Istanbul, Mombasa, Dar es Salaam, Lusaka and Harare. &ldquo;Our guests will now be able to enjoy flights to Cairo either directly from Nairobi or through Entebbe or Khartoum,&rdquo; Kenya Airways group managing director Sebastian Mikosz said.He said that the partnership will benefit member countries by enhancing bilateral trade as well as offering passengers more seamless connectivity between the two states.